      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WINE LOVER (2) was safely held in tougher company last start after settling off pace at Warragul, but prior to that won by half a length at Traralgon (24.77) beating Jairon Bale in a Bottom Up - Grade 5 on June 8. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Has winning claims on his best figures. WEIRD KAREN (1) has been out of the placings the last couple but was a T3 RSTW winner (24.42) three back at Traralgon. Can find the frame this time. OUR MABEL (4) finds it hard to win. Finished in the money last time though when second (25.06) at this track. The form out of her last race has been franked. Can measure up. DAINTREE BULLET (5) profiles nicely over this trip.",
